The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Trader found murdered
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Trader found murdered
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A scrap dealer was found murdered at his South Road home in Santoshpur, on Wednesday morning, his wrist slit. Police suspect Moinuddin Sardar was also strangulated.        
	The trader might have been killed by someone close to him. The door of his room was locked from outside. The items inside were untouched, said a senior officer of Jadavpur (east) police station. The cause of death can be ascertained only after the post-mortem report comes.        
	Moinuddin, in his mid-40s, lived on the ground floor of a two-storeyed house. His elder brother lives with his family on the first floor.        
	The body was spotted by Moinuddins nephew. I went to call my uncle but the room was locked from outside. Peeping through the window, I saw him lying on the bed. I called out to him but there was no response. I then noticed blood on the bed and raised an alarm, said Bittu Sardar.         
	The family immediately informed the police who broke open the door.        
	Moinuddin ran a small outlet of scrap material on the same premises as his house. South Road residents said he had been been living there for years. Neighbours said he was on good terms with everybody. The sleuths suspect the killing was intentional. They had no intention of stealing anything, said an officer.                                                                                                                                                                         
